# 📦 Supply Chain Data Analysis Project

## 📌 Project Overview
This project focuses on analyzing a Supply Chain dataset using Python to extract business insights related to product performance, suppliers, logistics, and quality control.

---

## 📊 Objectives
- Analyze product sales and revenue trends  
- Evaluate supplier performance  
- Compare shipping carriers and transportation modes  
- Study quality inspection results  
- Identify correlations between business variables  

---

## 🧰 Tools & Technologies
- Python  
- Pandas  
- Matplotlib  
- Jupyter Notebook  

---

## 📁 Dataset Features
- Product Type  
- Revenue Generated  
- Supplier Name  
- Shipping Costs & Times  
- Defect Rates  
- Manufacturing Costs  
- Transportation Modes  

---

## 🔍 Key Analysis Performed

### 1. Data Cleaning
- Handled formatting issues
- Rounded financial values
- Standardized text columns

### 2. Product Analysis
- Revenue by product type  
- Sales distribution across categories  

### 3. Supplier Analysis
- Defect rate comparison  
- Lead time evaluation  
- Cost efficiency analysis  

### 4. Logistics Analysis
- Shipping carrier performance  
- Transport mode comparison  

### 5. Quality Analysis
- Inspection result distribution  
- Supplier-wise quality performance  

### 6. Correlation Analysis
- Relationship between cost, price, and revenue  

---

## 📈 Key Insights
- Some suppliers have significantly higher defect rates  
- Transportation mode impacts shipping cost efficiency  
- Product type strongly influences revenue generation  

---

## 🚀 Conclusion
This project demonstrates how data analytics can improve decision-making in supply chain operations by identifying inefficiencies and optimizing performance.

